results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
First time I'd run across this species and it was in nymph form.  Hopefully I'll find an adult some day.  Was not expecting such a young one in November.  Check out the teeny tiny baby wings on its back.  Nice camouflage for being on a dead leaf.
ID confirmed in bugguide here by Brandon Woo:  https://bugguide.net/node/view/1471496
@brandonwoo
